          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Artem Blagodarenko",
          "email": "artem_blagodarenko@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2013-04-23 09:40:27.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Bob Glossman",
          "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-05-17 17:52:21.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-3219 ost: Ensure dirty flushed on fiemap ioctl",
        "message": "LU-3219 ost: Ensure dirty flushed on fiemap ioctl\n\nData corruption is possible if cp(coreutils) uses FIEMAP to obtain\ndata holes in shared file, since there could be dirty cache on\nother clients which hasn't been flushed back.\n\nTo ensure all the dirty on remote clients being flushed back on\nfiemap ioctl, we'd acquire ldlm lock on server side for fiemap,\nunless the local client (which invoke fiemap) has cached lock.\n\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-1001\nSigned-off-by: Artem Blagodarenko <artem_blagodarenko@xyratex.com>\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I6debe07acd015eb990d5b3748e50cc88d61065f8\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
